I criticized every important aspect, no Phoenix Wright isn’t a bad game, it’s how you play it to be as realistic as you wish it to be, yes, a hentai can try realism without going 100% but you cannot act as if nobody is going to ask questions. Everything will be questioned no matter how small or how stupid the subject, but when you plan to make something that’s mostly plot and realistic as possible, normally you tend to go all out and make it as interesting and realistic as possible. It’s what attracts the attention of people wanting more out of a story. In this story, it’s bland as hell, and nobody is really gonna look forward for part 2 being any better. Think of it like how people saw Pokémon Sword & Shield DLC. Barely any shit in the 1st DLC, and the 2nd didn’t have much to either neither. But y’know, that’s just my opinion and you have yours.
